.TH "LIGHTNING-LNURL" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-lnurl \- LNURL flows (LUD-01, 06, 12)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning lnurl
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning lnurl — LNURL flows (LUD-01, 06, 12).

Implements: LNURL per FEAT-173.
  share/doc/lightning/standards/lnurl-rfc/lud-06.md
  share/doc/lightning/standards/lnurl-rfc/lud-12.md

Subcommands:
  decode <lnurl>
  pay    <lnurl-or-address> <sat> [--comment <text>]

LNURL-withdraw and LNURL-auth are deferred to a follow-on.
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning lnurl <subcommand> [args]

   LNURL flows (LUD-01, LUD-06, LUD-12): bech32-encoded URLs that
   abstract a payment protocol behind a single string. Currently
   supports decode and pay; LNURL-withdraw and LNURL-auth are
   deferred. Accepts both bech32 LNURLs (LNURL1…) and Lightning
   Addresses (user@domain). Each sub-command also accepts --help.

subcommands:
   decode <lnurl>
   pay    <lnurl-or-address> <sat> [--comment <text>]
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
